        <section>

            <h2>About TheiaMath</h2>

            <p>
                TheiaMath is an open-source Java mathematics library focused on
                simplicity, precision, and developer experience.
            </p>

            <p>
                The project aims to provide a modern mathematical toolkit that
                can be used in educational, scientific, engineering, and
                general-purpose software projects.
            </p>

            <p>
                From basic arithmetic operations to future advanced algebraic
                systems, TheiaMath seeks to become a complete mathematical
                platform while remaining easy to learn and integrate.
            </p>

        </section>

        <section>

            <h2>Features</h2>

            <ul>

                <li>Arithmetic operations</li>

                <li>Algebra utilities</li>

                <li>Geometry tools</li>

                <li>Mathematical constants</li>

                <li>JavaDoc documentation</li>

                <li>High precision support</li>

                <li>Experimental BigDecimal integration</li>

                <li>Open source development</li>

            </ul>

        </section>

